How to use a Raspberry Pi without A monitor !
Headless Pi Set Up
Target : Pi Zero
My VNC LICENSE KEY : KD264-D4RY3-F2ERH-72F6N-A9V3A

ON THE PI ZERO (Ironically the Pi will need to be connected to a monitor for the following steps) : 


1) Download Hardware to make Pi headless from VNC :

					https://www.realvnc.com/download/vnc/raspberrypi/



2) Open the Terminal type :
					cd Downloads
3) Then Type :

					tar xvf [VNV FILE NAME].tar.gz
	
4) After Type :

					sudo dpkg -i [VNC Server Package name].deb [VNC Viewer package name ].deb

5) Copy the License key then type:
					sudo vnclicense -add KD264-D4RY3-F2ERH-72F6N-A9V3A

6) Type:
					vncserver 

7) PASSSWORD : raspberry 

8) Note the Display number 

ON YOUR COMPUTER:

9) Download VNC Viewer on your COMPUTER from

 					https://www.realvnc.com/download/viewer/

10) Connect With raspberry:[numberHere]
